Melania and Donald Trump send their greetings to Muslims as they celebrate Eid al-Fitr. They acknowledge the efforts of Muslims in the United States and around the world during the holy month of Ramadan to focus on acts of faith and charity. They also highlight the tradition of helping neighbors and breaking bread with people from all walks of life. The importance of mercy, compassion, and goodwill is emphasized during this holiday, and the United States renews its commitment to honoring these values. The message concludes with "Eid Mubarak," a traditional greeting for Eid.